Part 4/6
Risk Profiling Questionnaire






How many years remain before your retirement? 


Up to 3 years
More than 3 years, up to 5 years


More than 5 years, up to 8 years
More than 8 years, up to 15 years


More than 15 years





What is the percentage of your monthly saving in relation to your income (include salary and income from other sources)? 


0%
More than 0%, up to 10%


More than 10%, up to 20%
More than 20%, up to 40%


More than 40%





The total of your liquid asset (e.g. bank deposits and Exchange Fund Bills and Notes) is about ____ time(s) of your monthly salary: 


Less than 1
1 to 2


> 2 to 3
> 3 to 4


More than 4







Prev.
Next





Part 5/6
Risk Profiling Questionnaire






When you make an investment decision (for retirement purpose if MPF clients), which of the following considerations is most important to you?


Safety or emergency
Wealth Protection with sufficient liquidity


Wealth Preservation (return matching inflation)
Wealth Accumulation (return exceeding inflation)


Wealth Maximization





How would you best describe your expected salary or earnings in the next five years? 


I expect my salary will increase by more than 10% per annum.
I expect my salary will increase by 5% to 10% per annum.


I expect to have a positive salary increase of less than 5%.
I expect my salary will stay at the same level.


I expect my salary or earnings will decrease.





During the past 3 years, which securities listed below have you purchased? (you may select more than 1 choice)


Bank deposits, Exchange Fund Bills and Notes (EFBN) and money market funds
Bonds and bond funds


Stocks or stock funds from developed countries
Stocks or stock funds from developing countries


Derivatives and structured products







Prev.
Next





Part 6/6
Risk Profiling Questionnaire






What is your knowledge in investments?


None - I have no knowledge of financial markets or investment products.


Low - I only have some basic knowledge of financial markets and financial products.(e.g. basic features of stocks and bonds)


Low to Medium – I have adequate knowledge of financial market and financial products.(e.g. advanced features of stocks and bonds, such as volatility)


Medium to high – I have adequate investment knowledge and pay attention to financial news.


High - I am familiar with most financial products and attend investment talks regularly.(at least once a year)




Please indicate which statement best describes your risk attitude when you face a significant price fluctuation (e.g. volatility > 10%)?


I worry about price fluctuation and am willing to accept low return to avoid risk.


I have some concern about price fluctuation and am willing to accept less return to avoid most of the risk.


I am willing to accept some price fluctuation if I get a reasonable return.


I am willing to accept high price fluctuation to get a good return.


I can tolerate very high price fluctuation to maximize return.




Please estimate the overall volatility of your investments (exclude your first property but include other properties):


Up to 5%
More than 5%, up to 10%


More than 10%, up to 20%
More than 20%, up to 30%


More than 30%







Prev.
